{
  "texts": [
    "But what if, as encouraged by Alex et al. (2021), a model is trained on test set features without test set labels?",
    "This paper studies this question for the domain of few-shot text classification.",
    "NLP benchmarks for few-shot learning are prevalent, as having only a handful of labeled examples is more realistic.",
    "One consideration when designing these benchmarks is that some few-shot approaches can-at least theoretically-use unlabeled text from the test set.",
    "With Pattern-Exploiting Training (Schick and Schütze, 2021), for example, one can train the final classifier on test set text with soft labels predicted by an ensemble of supervised models."
  ]
}